result.execSummary:
On one or more charges, the deferred prosecution or sentencing agreement(s) on this case were fulfilled, and the charge(s) were dismissed.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.descr: Records of prosec. are converted data. See file.

records.addlTxt: The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.

Case Called @ 1:44 PM: Defendant Zachary Joseph Long in court.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Advised of right of Counsel.  Def does not wish to have counsel today and requests to speak with the State on resolution without counsel.   NGP entered by Court.   Court orders $200 Cash Bond w/conditions.  Off Record for ADA to meet with Def.  Back of Record and case recalled @ 3:03 pm:  Per ADA:  Defendant to enter plea today to Ct No 1 with 12 mos PPDA.    Def agrees with State's recital.   Defendant advised of right to counsel.  Court accepts voluntary waiver of counsel.  Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained.  Consequences explained for failure to abide by terms of PPDA. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea Ct 1 (POT):  NC  Court accepts plea and stays JOC.  Ct 2 (POP) DRI.  Court accepts terms and conditions of PPDA.  Matter stayed for 12 mos.  Def advised that bond continues during pendency of PPDA.
